name: India Palace
comment: Only one bathroom in this place, and it's a one-seater.  Food is pretty good... naan was a little greasy!

comment: This is the Unitarian Universalist Congregation of the Upper Valley, a Welcoming Congregation.  Accessible unless the ramp hasn't been shoveled free of snow.  Ask anyone present on entry.  Hold the handle down for a full flush.  http://www.uucuv.org/

name: Starbucks

name: Gates Hillman Center, Carnegie Mellon University
directions: On the Hillman side of the building, there is a single-seat, unisex restroom two doors down from room 4401.  If you're coming in from the street, turn left when you get to the glass windows, and then left again when you get to the door to 4401.  The bathroom is on your right.
comment: When the building was built, there was no official sign next to the bathroom, but it had a printed paper sign that said \"Men/Women Restroom\" on it.

name: W. M. Keck Science Center
directions: The bathroom is on the 1st floor in the far west side of the building.
comment: Expect the building to be open (at least) 8am to 5pm when school is in session.

directions: The building has an accessible entrance on the north side, and there is an elevator in the lobby. There are two single stall, locking bathrooms in the basement. One is marked men's and one is marked women's.
comment: Expect the building to be open 9-5 M-F, and during services and events.

name: Ralphs Westpark
directions: Walk into the store and straight down aisle seven.
comment: 24 Hour store. The bathrooms are checked every hour for cleanliness.

comment: hours are from like, 8am to midnight 7 days a week

directions: Left rear, past the deli counter
comment: 6 am to 11 pm seven days a week.  Interesting graffiti.Generally a gender-liberal area.

directions: Straight to the back of the store (left of the counter).

name: Myung Dong Tofu Cabin

comment: Wow, these are clean bathrooms. And no odor. And the food is good here too.

directions: There are two single-stalls near the back of the building, one non-gendered, one female-only.
comment: Please order something, even if it's just a lemonade to go. This is a great casual walk-in restaurant.

directions: Follow directions to the Merry-Go-Round. Drive past the Merry-Go-Round to the farthest parking lot. It's to the North of the parking lots.
comment: 10 stalls, 4 accessible ones. Griffith Park is very popular. They can get overused and dirty on the weekends.

name: CDGLCC
directions: Basement is handicap accessibly and gender neutral. There's one on the first floor and one on the third floor.
comment: Building is open to the public Sunday-Friday from 7-10pm .... the building is the Capital District Gay and Lesbian COmmunity Center.

name: The Fish Gallery
directions: On the back wall between the LG salt fish (not inverts) and chiclid sections
comment: We are T-friendly, Come in and injoy our relaxing showroom, shop for fish, ask questions, or just go to the bathroom. We also offer installation and service for your aqarium

name: Valero Station
directions: This is a gas station/convenience store across the street from a big cinema complex. There's one bathroom, gender free, a door that locks, a sink and a toilet. Walk in the front door, the bathroom's pretty much straight ahead at the back of the store.

name: WWU
directions: on the first floor as you walk in the building from the rose garden.  across the hall form the HR job posting board.

name: Caribou Coffee
street: 2111 Snelling Avenue North, St Paul, MN‎
directions: Across Snelling from HarMar Mall, on frontage road on west side of Snelling, in strip mall south County Road B

name: Marc's Sports Grill
directions: In the karaoke side of the bar at the very end
comment: One of very few multi-use unisex bathrooms in Arizona, all the stalls are very private and anyone of any gender or in between can use them.

name: Marc's Sports Grill
directions: In the karaoke side of the bar at the very end
comment: One of very few multi-use unisex bathrooms in Arizona, all the stalls are very private and anyone of any gender or in between can use them.

directions: Go straight to the back of the store and make a left - it is like a regular bathroom at home without the bathtub.
comment: This is an LGBT bookstore and espresso bar and the staff is used to seeing transgender/genderqueer people in their store.Hours are usually Mon. thur Sat. 10am to 9pm, Sundays 10am to 6pm.

name: WWU Campus Services Center
directions: Main Floor to the a little to your right & down the hall. Single occupancy gendered bathrooms
comment: Sorry don't have the exact address so map probably won't show right location. It's the  parking office, police office & health center for WWU. Next building south of the Rec center.

name: WWU Recreation Center
directions: Main floor: from front doors walk to front desk & take a right. There are two unisex bathrooms on your right. If you are a student or gym member, there is also a 'family changing room' in back that is gender neutral.

name: Osaka Japanese Restaurant
comment: Good sushi

name: Baba Yega
directions: rear of the dining areas ... this is a restaurant
comment: located in Houston's "artsy" district ... a comfortable place with good food and drink and reasonable prices; crowd is mixed urban gay/straight/other

name: quality burgers
directions: sw corner of 1st and east end, directly across 1st street from railroad tracks.  note there is construction on east end but restaurant is still open as of 15 feb 2007
comment: nice restaurant...persian owner, really neat fellow :)

name: fantastic cafe
directions: n side of 17th street w of wendys between grand ave and tustin ave

name: Dieseth Hall, Decorah
directions: If you are entering from the campus side, take a right through the wooden doors. Look immediately to your right, bathroom is in the corner.
comment: Open 24 hours a day, but the building is locked from 10pm to 8am.

name: Larsen Hall, Luther College
directions: Walking in from the front entrance by the street, you take a right, go through a door, and then turn left. You should see the Study Abroad Office in front of you. Right before the office on the left is a 'Unisex' bathroom, two stalls, they lock.
comment: Open all the time, but the building itself is locked from 10pm to 8am. Fairly queer friendly campus, especially considering its in Iowa and religiously affiliated. If you have trouble finding the building, ask around.

name: Kum n' Go
directions: Walk in the doors, and it's in the back-left corner of the gas station.
comment: Open 24 hours a day, people might eye you up if you look real genderqueer, but it's safe. (local queers prefer it to Casey's down the road)

name: Portland State University School of Social Work
directions: Take right out of elevator. Take another right at first hall way past the info desk. Bathroom on the right kinda tucked into a corner by janitor closet.

name: Good Vibrations, OE
directions: two bathrooms downstairs; two upstairs.
comment: they are clean and smell nice, and are used by the staff at Good Vibrations.

name: Downtown Flames
directions: All the way at the back of the dining area, on the ground floor.
comment: It's clean and nice, though it's only open for 6ish hours in the vicinity of lunchtime. The food is tasty so you should probably get something while you're there, or at least leave something in the tip jar.

name: Lillian Massey building
directions: 1st floor, next to the staircase, also 2nd floor, take a left then another left, through the doors, around the corner.

name: Wild Oats Natural Marketplace
directions: In the back of the store.
comment: There is one men's room and one women's room, both single stall and lockable.Hours:Mon-Sat 7:30a.m.-10.00p.m.Sun 8a.m.-9p.m.

name: Unitarian Society
directions: Downstairs in the Unitarian Society -- accessible entrance on side, with elevator access to basement level.
comment: The building is usually locked.  These bathrooms are available to people who attend events at the Society.Bathrooms are labled Men/Transgender/Accessible, and Women/Transgender/Accessible.  The assumption is that people will self identify however they want, and no one freaks out.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: In the far right corner of the back as you come in the front door. There is probably a pile of merchandise by the hallway; unless you know there's a bathroom there, you might not notice it.

name: Longs Drugs
directions: Back of building near Pharmacy on right side
comment: Single stall public restroom near Hwy 99

name: Lowes

name: King's Books
directions: Right side of the store, a little back from the entrance.
comment: I think this may require a key, but I seem to remember using it without buying anything.  When I lived in the area, they had a visibly gender-variant employee, and are very liberal, so if you were to tell them your reason for going there, I do not think they would require you to shop.

name: Stanford Bookstore
directions: 1st floor, in the back of the store

name: Angel's

name: Jin Ju

comment: closed Mondays; sexy wait staff; great food and cocktails

name: Giovanni's Room
directions: On 2nd floor - ask for key at desk.

name: Monona Terrace Convention Center
directions: On the 4th floor (the main floor, entering from the Square), there are 'family' bathrooms which are locking bathrooms, usually furnished with a chair in addition to the usual amenities. They are located on either end of the building, between the Men's and Women's. I believe that there is at least one more on the ground floor inside the exhibit hall.

name: Brattleboro Food Co-op
comment: Seven days  8am to 9pm

comment: The Lucy Parsons Center is a radical bookstore and community center that is friendly towards gender ambiguous people. Books on gender issues are amongst the media sold there.

name: Daedalus
directions: Two upstairs, one down.  Nicest is the downstairs one.
comment: A classy bathroom with a strong centrifugal force flush.  I'd drop the kids off at the pool there any day.  However, you should really only use it if you're a patron - people don't run in and out of the place.  Plus, the owners are wicked, wicked nice, so you should at least have a drink.

name: Sears
directions: In the back of the store.  They will let you use it if you ask, but you should probably be a serious shopper.

name: Walmart
directions: There's a family restroom in the back of the store, with layaway and gendered restrooms.

street: First Wok Take Out, Wal-Mart Mall, South end of Mt. Pleasant off Mission Street
directions: Go to the First Wok Take out Chinese Restaurant, the unisex bathroom is to the right of the ordering counter.
comment: The food is also very good with free hot tea, and inexpensive, so enjoy the friendly atmosphere while you are there.

name: Wok &Teriyaki
directions: In the Tacoma/ Top Foods strip mall on S. 23rd and Union, a couple of doors down on the left from Top Foods.
comment: The restaurant is good, the staff is nice, and no one pays any attention to which gendered single stall bathroom one walks into. I've used both of them interchangeably.

name: University of Iowa Main Library
directions: First floor, between the information desk and the exhibition area.
comment: This is a gender-free, locking, single-stall, wheelchair accessible restroom with a baby changing station in a building that stays open later than most on campus.

name: H2O Cafe
directions: in the back
comment: free, fast wifi

name: California Shakespeare Theater/ Bruns Amphitheater
comment: A long row of individual/ locking stalls are available to theater patrons of any gender. My guess is that it was instituted to ease congestion during intermission pee breaks.For those who dig Shakespearian theater in a great out-door setting, you can enjoy the show and, at breaks, feel free to pee!

name: Cooper Hall
directions: 2nd (?) floor of Cooper Hall, ungendered single stall locking.I just came across this website, and editing this to say, yes, it's on the 2nd floor and there's another ungendered single stall locking bathroom on the fourth floor. :)

name: TIHAN
directions: In the front office.

name: Byerly's grocery / restaurant
directions: Roseville is a 1st tier suberb of St. PaulThe locking restroom is located between the restaurant and grocery sections, immediately off the parking lot entrance.
comment: Store is open 24/7. As an elderly hetro male, with a very 'senior member' I often have to deal with a certain reluctance on the part of said member, exacerbated by the presence of extraneous noises. Therefore I prefer a bit of privacy.Sometimes, things take as long as they take.

name: Friendly St. Market
